---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Updated Child Support Rules · Pro Se Fair Play Mediation"
  description="If you're getting divorced, establishing paternity, or modifying child support, here's what you need to know about Florida's child support laws in 2026."
>
  <!-- ========================== HEADER ========================== -->
  <header class="article-header">
    <div class="container article-header-inner">
      <p class="kicker reveal reveal-d1">
        <span class="kicker-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        Florida Family Law
      </p>
      <h1 class="display article-title reveal reveal-d2">
        Updated <span class="title-keep"><span class="display-italic">Child Support</span> Rules<span class="display-italic">.</span></span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede reveal reveal-d3">
        If you're getting divorced, establishing paternity, or modifying child
        support, here's what you need to know about Florida's child support
        laws in 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ========================== BODY ========================== -->
  <section class="article-body">
    <div class="container-narrow article-prose">
      <h2>How Is Child Support Calculated?</h2>
      <p>
        Florida uses the Income Shares Model, which means both parents share the
        financial responsibility of raising their child.
      </p>
      <p>The court looks at things like:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Each parent's income</li>
        <li>The number of overnight visits each parent has</li>
        <li>Health insurance costs</li>
        <li>Childcare expenses</li>
        <li>The number of children</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These guidelines are found in Florida Statute § 61.30.</p>

      <h2>What's New in 2026?</h2>

      <h3>Courts Must Follow the Guidelines More Closely</h3>
      <p>
        Judges are less likely to order child support above or below the
        guideline amount unless there is a very good reason. If they do, they
        must explain their decision in writing.
      </p>

      <h3>Parenting Time Matters More Than Ever</h3>
      <p>
        The more overnights a parent spends with the child, the more that may
        affect child support. In many cases, increased parenting time can lower
        a parent's child support obligation.
      </p>

      <h3>Changes for Paternity Cases</h3>
      <p>
        Beginning July 1, 2026, new procedures help streamline child support in
        paternity cases involving children born to unmarried parents.
      </p>

      <h3>Easier Court Access</h3>
      <p>Many Florida family courts now allow:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Electronic filing (e-Filing)</li>
        <li>Virtual hearings by Zoom</li>
        <li>Online submission of financial documents</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This makes the court process faster and more convenient for many
        families.
      </p>

      <h3>Child Support Can Be Modified</h3>
      <p>
        If your financial situation changes significantly, or your parenting
        schedule changes, you may be able to ask the court to modify your child
        support order.
      </p>

      <h2>How Is Child Support Enforced?</h2>
      <p>
        If child support is not paid, Florida has several enforcement options,
        including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Wage garnishment</li>
        <li>Driver's license suspension</li>
        <li>Intercepting federal tax refunds</li>
        <li>Other collection methods through the Florida Department of Revenue</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Mediation Can Help</h2>
      <p>
        Instead of asking a judge to decide everything, many parents choose
        mediation. Mediation gives parents the opportunity to work together to
        create parenting and financial agreements that fit their family's
        unique needs while staying within Florida law.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================== CLOSING CTA ========================== -->
  <section class="article-cta">
    <div class="container-narrow article-cta-inner">
      <a class="btn btn-primary article-cta-btn" href="/book">
        Book a Free, Private Consultation
        <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     HEADER — cream, mirrors the legal pages
     ============================================================ */
  .article-header {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: clamp(4rem, 6vw + 1rem, 6rem) clamp(2rem, 3vw, 3rem);
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, rgba(196, 154, 75, 0.08), transparent 55%),
      var(--color-cream);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .article-header-inner { position: relative; max-width: 64rem; }
  .article-title {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: var(--step-5);
    line-height: 1.04;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    max-width: 20ch;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .article-title .display-italic { color: var(--color-gold-deep); font-weight: 400; }
  /* Keep "Child Support Rules." together so it drops as one block
     ("Updated" / "Child Support Rules.") on desktop. */
  .article-title .title-keep { white-space: nowrap; }
  .article-header .lede {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }

  /* ============================================================
     BODY PROSE
     ============================================================ */
  .article-body {
    padding-block: var(--space-lg) var(--space-3xl);
    background: var(--color-cream);
  }
  .article-prose {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
  .article-prose p { max-width: 64ch; }
  .article-prose p + p,
  .article-prose ul + p { margin-top: 1.25rem; }
  .article-prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .article-prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: none;
  }
  .article-prose h3 {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 24;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .article-prose ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .article-prose li { line-height: 1.55; }
  .article-prose strong { color: var(--color-navy); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ============================================================
     CLOSING CTA — button only
     ============================================================ */
  .article-cta {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-cream-warm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
  }
  .article-cta::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 0 auto 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--color-gold) 40%, var(--color-gold) 60%, transparent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .article-cta-inner { display: flex; justify-content: center; }
  .article-cta-btn {
    background: var(--color-navy);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-navy);
  }
  .article-cta-btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-navy-deep);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 1.8rem + 3vw, 3.5rem); }
    /* On phones, let the title wrap freely (balanced) instead of forcing
       the desktop one-block break. */
    .article-title .title-keep { white-space: normal; }
  }
</style>
